author: news@courierpublicationsllc.com (Staff)
title: Husson's Wickenden cards NAC rookie-of-year honors
text:
Husson's Wickenden cards NAC rookie-of-year honors By Staff | Oct 14, 2015 
Bangor â€” Husson University freshman Daulton Wickenden wrapped up his first year of college golf in style as he nabbed the 2015 North Atlantic Conference rookie-of-the-year award. 
Wickenden, who was named first-team all-conference in the NAC, shot 73 on day one and 76 on day two at the NAC men's golf championship, as the former Windjammer finished second overall in the tournament. 
He placed behind teammate Greg Martin, who finished first and was named NAC player of the year. 
Wickenden finished no lower than eighth in four of the invitationals the Eagles competed in, with his best performance coming at the Maine Intercollegiate Golf Championship, where he took medalist honors after shooting 4-under par. 
Wickenden nabbed NAC rookie-of-week honors four times this season and NAC player of week once. 
Wickenden, a 2015 Camden Hills Regional High School graduate, was a terrific golfer four years, including helping lead the Windjammers to state Class B championships in 2013 and 2014. He also played baseball for the Windjammers and was one of the team's top pitchers, for a squad that reached the state Class B title game last spring.
